'''Patanjali Ayurved Limited,''' is an [[List of companies of India|Indian]] [[Final good|consumer goods]] [[company]], [[Manufacturing|manufacturing units]] and headquarters are located in the industrial area of [[Haridwar, Uttarakhand]] while the registered office is located at [[Delhi]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/430-acres-allotted-to-Patanjali/article16984837.ece|title=430 acres allotted to Patanjali|last=Aradhak|first=Purusharth|work=The Hindu |language=en |accessdate=26 February 2017}}</ref> The company manufactures [[mineral]] and [[herbal]] products. According to [[CLSA]] and [[HSBC]], Patanjali is the fastest growing [[Fast-moving consumer goods|FMCG]] company in [[India]]. It is valued at {{INRConvert|3000|c|lk=|year=2016}} and some predict revenues of {{INRConvert|5000|c}} for the fiscal 2015–16.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/are-pes-bending-over-backwards-to-invest-in-patanjali/article8093259.ece|title=Are PEs bending over backwards to invest in Patanjali?|publisher=The Hindu|date=11 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.indiainfoline.com/article/news-top-story/india-consumer-patanjali-is-disrupting-india%E2%80%99s-consumer-space-116020600292_1.html|title=Patanjali is disrupting India's consumer space|publisher=IIFL|date=6 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/hsbc-global-rsearch-cuts-target-prices-of-britannia-dabur-and-nestle-between-6-and-16-says-patanjali/articleshow/50868122.cms|title=HSBC Global Rsearch cuts target prices of Britannia Dabur and Nestle between 6% and 16%, says Patanjali|publisher=Economic Times|date=5 February 2016}}</ref>
Patanjali declared its annual turnover of the year 2016–17 to be estimated {{INR Convert|10216|c}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wap.business-standard.com/article-amp/markets/wap.business-standard.com/article/companies/ramdev-s-patanjali-doubles-sales-to-rs-10-561-crore-in-fy17-117050400652_1.html|title=Ramdev's Patanjali shakes up FMCG order; next up 'nutritious restaurants'|work=Business Standard|accessdate=15 July 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170715102827/http://wap.business-standard.com/article-amp/markets/wap.business-standard.com/article/companies/ramdev-s-patanjali-doubles-sales-to-rs-10-561-crore-in-fy17-117050400652_1.html|archivedate=15 July 2017|author=Arnab Dutta|date=5 May 2017}}</ref> It was listed 13th in the list of [[India]]'s most trusted brands ([[The Brand Trust Report]]) as of 2018, and ranks first in [[FMCG]] category.<ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.drivespark.com/four-wheelers/2018/most-trusted-automobile-brands-tata-maruti-honda-bmw-025511.html|title=India’s Most Trusted Brands 2018 — Tata, Maruti, Honda & BMW Among The Most Trusted Auto Brands|accessdate=February 1, 2020}}</ref>

==History==
[[Ramdev]] baba established the Patanjali Ayurved Limited in 2006 along with [[Acharya Balkrishna|Balkrishna]], with the objective of establishing science of [[Ayurveda]] in accordance and coordination with the latest technology and ancient wisdom.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://patanjaliayurved.net/faqs.php#accordionOne|title=Patanjali Ayurved FAQ's|publisher=Patanjali Ayurverd|access-date=22 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160207150846/https://patanjaliayurved.net/faqs.php#accordionOne|archive-date=7 February 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2015/01/13/ramdev-consumer-products-_n_6460760.html|title=Baba Ramdev's Business Empire Soars, With His Own Rising Profile|publisher=HuffPost India}}</ref><ref>[http://www.business-standard.com/article/management/the-patanjali-effect-116020800204_1.html] "The Patanjali effect" Business-Standard</ref>

[[Balkrishna]] owns 98.6% of Patanjali Ayurved, and as of March 2018, has a net worth of ₹43,932 [[crore]] (US$6.1 billion).<ref name="Forbes profile">{{cite web|title=Forbes profile: Acharya Balkrishna|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/acharya-balkrishna/|website=Forbes|accessdate=16 March 2018}}</ref>

