==Production==
Patanjali Food and Herbal Park at [[Haridwar]] is the main production facility operated by Patanjali Ayurved. The company has a production capacity of {{INRConvert|35000|c|lk=|year=2018}} and is in the process of  expanding to a capacity of {{INRConvert|60000|c|lk=|year=2016}} through its new production units at several places, including [[Noida]], [[Nagpur]], and [[Indore]].<ref name=bs0517/><ref>{{cite news|publisher=Web Dunia|url=http://hindi.webdunia.com/international-hindi-news/baba-ramdev-herbal-factory-herbal-products-nepal-kathmandu-115041800030_1.html|title=Ramdev to open herbal factory in Nepal|date=18 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://insighttvnews.com/newsdetails.php?show=83816|title=Patanjali herbal park in Nepal|publisher=Insight TV News Network|date=28 February 2015}}</ref>

In 2016, the Patanjali Food and Herbal Park was given a full-time security cover of 35 armed [[Central Industrial Security Force]] (CISF) commandos.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/CISF-Team-to-Guard-Ramdevs-Food-Park/2016/03/09/article3317272.ece|title=CISF Team to Guard Ramdev's Food Park|place=NEW DELHI|first=Yatish|last=Yadav |date=9 March 2016 |publisher=Indian Express}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/india-news/ramdev-now-a-client-of-paramilitary-force-cisf-for-his-food-park-1285079|title=Ramdev's Food Park Gets Round-The-Clock Protection From Paramilitary CISF|first=Varun|last=Sharma |date=8 March 2016 |publisher=NDTV}}</ref><ref name="Tribune_India">{{cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/uttarakhand/ramdev-s-food-park-gets-full-time-cisf-cover/206339.html|title=Ramdev's food park gets full-time CISF cover |date=9 March 2016 |publisher=The Tribune India}}</ref> The park will be the eighth private institute in [[India]] to be guarded by [[Central Industrial Security Force|CISF]] paramilitary forces.<ref name="Tribune_India"/> [[Ramdev]] baba is himself a "Z" category protectee of central paramilitary forces.<ref name="Tribune_India"/>

In 2017, Patanjali group launched their official Caller Tune with their slogan 'Swadeshi swabhimaan, rashtra seva ka abhiyaan' music composed by [[Vaibhav Saxena]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailypioneer.com/2017/state-editions/swadeshi-ringtone-patanjali-aims-to-stretch-its-outreach.html|title=Swadeshi ringtone: Patanjali aims to stretch its outreach |date=30 August 2017 |publisher=The Pioneer}}</ref>

==Controversies==
===Suspension of Amla juice===
The Ministry of Defence's canteen stores department (CSD) had suspended the sale of Patanjali Ayurved's amla juice after receiving an adverse state-laboratory test report on the product.

The move came after the product was tested at the central food lab that found it to be 'unfit for consumption'. After which, the CSD asked all its depots to make debit notes for their existing stock so that the product can be returned.<ref>https://hindustantimes.com/india-news/baba-ramdev-s-patanjali-products-fail-uttarakhand-quality-test/story-bXo4XySEajw7ZDby4GISML.html</ref>
<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.businesstoday.in/lite/story/defence-canteens-remove-ramdevs-patanjali-amla-juice-after-adverse-lab-test-report/1/250631.html |title= Defence canteens remove Ramdev's Patanjali amla juice after adverse lab report|accessdate=18 May 2020}}</ref>

===Notice by FSSAI===
Patanjali launched [[instant noodles]] on 15 November 2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/business/ramdevs-patanjali-launches-noodles/article7884161.ece|title=Ramdev's Patanjali launches noodles|publisher=The Hindu|date=16 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://khabar.ibnlive.com/news/desh/baba-ramdev-maggie-fssai-notice-patanjali-428194.html|title=FSSAI sends notice to Baba Ramdev's company|work=ibnlive.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://navbharattimes.indiatimes.com/business/business-news/trouble-mounts-for-ramdevs-atta-noodles-fssai-issues-notice-to-patanjali-ayurved/articleshow/49870608.cms|title=Trouble mounts for Ramdev's Atta Noodles, FSSAI issues notice to Patanjali Ayurved|publisher=Navbharat Times}}</ref> [[Food Safety and Standards Authority of India]] slapped a notice on the company as neither Patanjali nor Aayush, which are the two brand names under which Patanjali got licenses, have got any approval for manufacturing instant noodles.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ndtv.com/india-news/no-approval-for-patanjali-instant-noodles-says-food-safety-regulator-1244771|title=No Approval for Patanjali Instant Noodles, Says Food Safety Regulator|publisher=NDTV|date=18 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/no-licence-for-noodles-fssai-slaps-showcause-on-patanjali/|title='No licence for noodles': FSSAI slaps showcause on Patanjali|date=21 November 2015|work=The Indian Express}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.oneindia.com/india/patanjali-s-atta-noodles-in-trouble-baba-ramdev-breaks-silence-modi-govt-controversy-1931379.html|title=Patanjali's Atta Noodles in trouble: Baba Ramdev breaks silence, drags Modi govt into controversy|publisher=oneindia.com|date=19 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.livehindustan.com/news/national/article1-will-reply-at-the-earliest-when-we-get-notice-baba-ramdev-505128.html|title=Patanjali Atta noodles gets notice|publisher=livehindustan.com}}</ref>

==Sales and distribution==
Patanjali Ayurved sells through nearly 4,700 retail outlets as of May 2016.<ref name=indiatimes/><ref name="The Economic Times">{{cite news|date=13 January 2015|title=Baba Ramdev expands empire beyond yoga to FMCG|publisher=[[The Economic Times]]|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-01-13/news/58024735_1_fmcg-business-fmcg-companies-patanjali-ayurved}}</ref> Patanjali also sells its products online and is planning to open outlets at [[Indian Railways|railway stations]] and [[List of airports in India|airports]].<ref name="India Today">{{Cite news|title=Ramdev's Patanjali Ayurved  enters big retail with Future Group tie-up|publisher=India Today|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/ramdevs-patanjali-ayurved-enters-big-retail-with-future-group-tie-up/1/495151.html}}</ref> Patanjali Ayurveda has tied up with Pittie Group and [[Kishore Biyani]]'s [[Future Group]] on 9 October 2015.<ref name=indiatimes/> As per the tie-up with [[Future Group]], all the consumer products of Patanjali will be available for the direct sale in [[Future Group]] outlets.<ref name="Nayi Duniya">{{cite news|date=9 October 2015|title=Ramdev products available in Big bazaar|publisher=Nayi Duniya|url=http://naidunia.jagran.com/business/commodity-baba-ramdev-signs-deal-with-future-group-503056}}</ref><ref name="Future group and Patanjali tie-up">{{cite news|date=9 October 2015|title=Future group and Patanjali tie-up|publisher=Patrika|url=http://www.patrika.com/news/industry/future-group-to-tie-up-with-baba-ramdev-s-patanjali-1117705}}</ref><ref name="The Hindu">{{cite news|date=9 October 2015|title=Future Group partners Patanjali Ayurveda|publisher=[[The Hindu]]|url=http://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/future-group-shares-gain-on-tieup-with-ramdevs-patanjali/article7743470.ece}}</ref> Patanjali Ayurveda products are also available in modern trade stores including [[Reliance Industries|Reliance retail]], [[HyperCity|Hyper city]] and Star Bazaar apart from online channels.<ref name=indiatimes/><ref name="Amar Ujala">{{cite news|date=18 December 2014|title=Patanjali products to be sold in Khadi bhandars|publisher=Amar Ujala|url=http://www.amarujala.com/feature/samachar/national/patanjali-prodocts-will-be-sold-on-khadi-bhandar-hindi-news-ss}}</ref><ref name="ABP Live">{{cite news|date=25 August 2015|title=Baba Ramdev's Patanjali Ayurveda to make, sell DRDO food products|publisher=ABP Live|url=http://www.abplive.in/india/2015/08/25/article694304.ece/Baba-Ramdevs-Patanjali-Ayurveda-to-make-sell-DRDO-food-products}}</ref><ref name="HuffPost India">{{cite news|date=24 August 2015|title=Baba Ramdev's Patanjali Ayurveda To Sell DRDO Food Products|publisher=HuffPost India|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2015/08/24/ramdev-drdo_n_8029430.html}}</ref><ref name="thehindu.com">[http://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/patanjali-ayurved-to-invest-rs-1150-crores/article8524025.ece] "Patanjali Ayurved to invest Rs 1,150 crores, eyes doubling revenue" The Hindu</ref> Patanjali Ayurved, co-founded by yoga guru [[Ramdev]], is targeting [[Indian rupee sign|₹]]10,000-[[crore]] revenue in 2016–17, after sales grew 150% in the previous financial year to [[Indian rupee sign|₹]]5,000 [[crore]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/baba-ramdev-s-patanjali-aims-to-double-its-revenue-to-rs-10-000-cr-in-2016-17-116042700061_1.html|title=Baba Ramdev's Patanjali aims to double its revenue to Rs 10,000 cr in 2016-17|first=Arnab|last=Dutta|date=27 April 2016|publisher=|accessdate=16 March 2018|via=Business Standard}}</ref>

